Description: Children's Artwork Sharing Website
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: RefrigeratorArtist.com provides a place for parents to save and share their children's artwork digitally. Parents can order customized products such as prints and t-shirts featuring the art, and enter one piece of their child's artwork in a monthly drawing for $400 in U.S. savings bonds. A portion of the profits goes toward art programs and education for children. The website, launched in October 2009, helps parents preserve and enjoy their children's art by storing and sharing it online. Pieces of art that would typically have been displayed on the family's fridge and eventually relegated to closets or a box in the attic can now be archived and shared with others for free. The site gives parents the option to share artwork via email or with their entire social network through Facebook integration. Parents can also invite their close friends and relatives to become their "friends" on RefrigeratorArtist.com. Whenever they add new art to their child's gallery, anyone they have "friended" will also be able to see the artwork when they visit the site. The site's mission, in addition to providing a modern web-based archival and sharing option for parents, is to celebrate and increase the role art plays in children's lives. A portion of all profits generated through product sales and site advertising will be donated to organizations dedicated to art programs and education for children. The founders feel strongly about the importance of such programs to children's development. Art participation has been proven to foster brain development and improve social skills, problem-solving skills, and test scores. Parents and relatives have the opportunity to create unique mementos and gifts from their children's art on the site as well. Customizable products such as mugs, posters, t-shirts, and magnets enable personalized gift-giving and keepsake creation. Another feature of the site is a monthly drawing with a prize of $400 in U.S. savings bonds for the winning artist. Each month parents may enter one piece of artwork per artist, and every vote the artwork receives from other site users will be another entry in the drawing, increasing the artist's chances of winning the savings bonds.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Community and Lifestyle

To display a Vid, select OPEN and select the Vid.  Quick!    To share a Vid, select SHARE, enter an email address and send.  Secure! VIDI creates a personal database containing an index to every item in every Vid so you quickly and easily recall any document, web-page, video or image. VIDI is secure because VIDI only shares the index to an item, not a copy of the item, so a recipient is only able to view an item if they have permission to access to the item.

In order to do this, Basic Solutions has a process that their clients are matched with the best engineers possible. Basic Solutions starts at the basics by understanding the requirements of a client and studying the job description as provided. When working with Cisco, constant communication the client manager is a necessary part of the process in understanding what kind of candidate and skills the team at Cisco are looking for. Utilizing smart hand support, Basic Solutions is able to assist in cases of data centers without resources. If something goes down, they ensure to have a team readily available that is able to fix the issue. This helps differentiate Basic Solutions from their competitors in being able to provide the exceptional customer experience that they’ve become well-known for. The pool of talent that Basic Solutions has to choose from are very technical and have the full experience. Basic Solutions has been working with some clients for more than 15 years, never having to focus on selling anything but rather providing suggestions and opportunities to further enhance their customer experience. One of the best parts of operating as a business is that Basic Solutions gets to work with some of the top companies and on some of the biggest projects in the world.
